# 8. Launch a shell from an alpine container, and make sure that you can interact 
#   directly with the container via your terminal, and that the container deletes 
#   itself once the shellâ€™s execution is done.

docker run --rm -it alpine /bin/sh


# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# note: 
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   -i -> interact (not closing)
#   -t -> tty, allocate a psuedo-TTY
#   shell -> is like a terminal 
#   to leave command : " exit "